# Summary
Remote evaluation in Amplitude Experiment involves making requests to evaluation servers to fetch variants for users, supporting advanced targeting capabilities like Amplitude ID resolution, IP geolocation, property canonicalization, behavioral cohort targeting, and historical user properties that aren't available in local evaluation.

